        <dcterms:dateSubmitted>2025-09-12 08:18:29</dcterms:dateSubmitted>
    </bib:Document>
    <bib:Memo rdf:about="#item_3">
        <rdf:value>&lt;div data-schema-version=&quot;9&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Note that the model can be used to aggregately represent any type of inverter-based resources, including distribution-connected storage distributed along a feeder.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Therefore, if this model is used to simulate distributed energy storage, it must be understood that it is not appropriate for simulations that span over a time period that is a significant portion of the charging/discharging capacity of the battery. For example, if a distributed energy storage device can provide many minutes to hours of power output (or charging), then in a 10- to 30-second simulation (typical of planning studies), there would be little impact on the state-of-charge of the battery—and so this model is adequate. However, if the battery energy storage device has only a few seconds worth of capacity, this model is not appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</rdf:value>
    </bib:Memo>
