        <dc:title>Static and transient load models taking account voltage and frequency dependence</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>The composition of loads in electrical grids has changed dramatically over the last few years. Nowadays numerous devices are connected via switching power supplies or other power electronic circuits. The distribution of energy-saving lamps is also progressing. Often studies about load behavior concentrate on static correlations between voltage and active or reactive power of devices. Transient processes after voltage steps are often neglected. Furthermore, the frequency is assumed as constant in most of these studies because frequency derivations seldom exceed a few mHz in electrical grids. In this paper both, the static and the transient behavior of selected loads in case of fast voltage and frequency changes are examined. Load models are presented and a new model is proposed which can be used to model the measured behavior in simulations as closely as possible.</dcterms:abstract>
        <dc:date>2016-06</dc:date>
        <z:libraryCatalog>IEEE Xplore</z:libraryCatalog>
